<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="21" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="21">
After the study of type material, the number of marginal papillae is not defined for 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. wassi" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="wassi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">S. wassi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pettibone, 1966. Their number might be the same as in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. ligneroi" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="ligneroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">S. ligneroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. described above, but better specimens are needed to clarify this. On the other hand, most diagnostic features for the species were confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolf, PS" journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/3248995" refId="B56" refString="Wolf, PS, 1984. .https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/3248995" url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/3248995" year="1984">Wolf (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, the fragility of anal cirri might explain why they were not observed by him.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
